A 48-year-old man has been arrested on two counts of murder for killing his girlfriend and another man on Monday.The deceased both from Mokopane were identified as Elliot Makalela, 49, and Sina Kgosana, 32-years-old.According to Lt Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe, &#8220;it is alleged that the suspect found his girlfriend and another man believed to be her other boyfriend inside the car at coener Retief and Pretorius street in Mokopane CBD and without saying anything, he shot both of them.&#8221;Whilst the motive behind the killings is still unknown to the police, the Mokopane police have not ruled out the case of a love triangle killing.The suspect is set to appear in court soon and police are still investigating this case.&nbsp;-Aviwe Maxheke